<div id="review_1399247959" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1399247959" />
    <a title="RelentlessBookChic Ramblings &amp; Reviews " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12941902-relentlessbookchic-ramblings-reviews"><img alt="RelentlessBookChic Ramblings &amp; Reviews " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1464483219p2/12941902.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1399247959?book_show_action=true">Sep 23, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="RelentlessBookChic Ramblings &amp; Reviews " class="user" itemprop="url" name="RelentlessBookChic Ramblings &amp; Reviews " href="/user/show/12941902-relentlessbookchic-ramblings-reviews">RelentlessBookChic Ramblings &amp; Reviews </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12941902-relentlessbookchic-ramblings-reviews?shelf=books-i-ve-read">books-i-ve-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12941902-relentlessbookchic-ramblings-reviews?shelf=tbr">tbr</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12941902-relentlessbookchic-ramblings-reviews?shelf=romantic-thriller">romantic-thriller</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1399247959" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13195385793275011321">Desecrating Solomon has a unique story line that will draw you in from page one. I think there may have been lapses of time where everything else ceased to exist while I was on this adventure in West Virginia. <br/><br/>Solomon &amp; Chaos are your primary characters; Solomon is a stand up dude. I like his sense of humor, his giving heart and his protective nature. Chaos is a bit on the strange side, naive and sheltered but there is still this strong willed woman beneath what she has been conditioned to be. <br/>T</span>
  <span id="freeText13195385793275011321" style="display:none">Desecrating Solomon has a unique story line that will draw you in from page one. I think there may have been lapses of time where everything else ceased to exist while I was on this adventure in West Virginia. <br /><br />Solomon &amp; Chaos are your primary characters; Solomon is a stand up dude. I like his sense of humor, his giving heart and his protective nature. Chaos is a bit on the strange side, naive and sheltered but there is still this strong willed woman beneath what she has been conditioned to be. <br />The subsidiary characters in this book are awesome. Between Miss Mary &amp; Jimmy I often felt like I was in a scene with some of my older relatives. They also helped to bring some comedic relief between some pretty intense and sometimes disturbing scenes. <br /><br />The story was well written, unpredictable and rich with plot twists, turns and pivots. You go from "Oh hell no" to "Are you fuckin' serious!" The character development is on point throughout the book; it isn't as if Solomon &amp; Chaos just fell for each other ..you actually get to see the falling. <br /><br />The background story is just as in depth and enthralling as the plot. The history of the asylum will blow your mind and the "realness" of the occult in this story is disturbing because it isn't that far fetched from reality. <br /><br />Amazing book that will literally have you both scared and anxious to turn the page. It is written well and in such a way that you will easily read it from beginning to end while tuning out the real world. Can't wait to read the next one. <br /><br />Relentless Book Chics approved &amp; recommended. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13195385793275011321" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


