<span id="freeTextContainer4770491389327567817">Yep. It&apos;s the build up that kills you. The part on the roller coaster where you are climbing and with every &quot;tick tick&quot; of the coaster climbing your heart beats faster and faster knowing the drop is coming. That was this first book. My heart was beating knowing the drop was coming. Knowing something big but then in Lucian Bane fashion...he leads you to the edge and says &quot;to be continued&quot;. Brat. However in this book we are introduced to many characters, all I&apos;m assuming, will play a big part in t</span>
  <span id="freeText4770491389327567817" style="display:none">Yep. It's the build up that kills you. The part on the roller coaster where you are climbing and with every "tick tick" of the coaster climbing your heart beats faster and faster knowing the drop is coming. That was this first book. My heart was beating knowing the drop was coming. Knowing something big but then in Lucian Bane fashion...he leads you to the edge and says "to be continued". Brat. However in this book we are introduced to many characters, all I'm assuming, will play a big part in this mystery of Luna Asylum. There are hints dropped here and there that leaves you with so many questions that you are dying to know the answers to. It's so easy to fall in love with Solomon. What an awesome character. Chaos/Silence my heart goes out to. I'm hoping Lucian starts to show a little bit of strength coming from her in the next book. I would love nothing more than to see her kick some major ...you know. This is a definite read! </span>
