        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1398450904" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10807571494068134044">Wow. This book has left me speechless. You could feel the pain and sadness throughout the entire book. Chaos has had a terrible life. She has been horribly brainwashed and you can&apos;t help but want to steal her away and protect her. Then here comes Solomon who has also had so much heartbreak. They bond together and he feels the need to protect her, save her, and love her. Little does he know how big the consequences of loving Chaos are. As I sat reading this I could picture every moment clearly as</span>
  <span id="freeText10807571494068134044" style="display:none">Wow. This book has left me speechless. You could feel the pain and sadness throughout the entire book. Chaos has had a terrible life. She has been horribly brainwashed and you can't help but want to steal her away and protect her. Then here comes Solomon who has also had so much heartbreak. They bond together and he feels the need to protect her, save her, and love her. Little does he know how big the consequences of loving Chaos are. As I sat reading this I could picture every moment clearly as if it were playing on a movie reel in front of me. I could picture everything clear as day as if I have lived the moments they are experiencing. The pain Chaos has had to deal with was gut wrenching. I wouldn't wish that on anyone. Solomon has his faith and it's amazing to be able to use that and really feel it. You cant help but feel what these people felt and go through during this entire book. I am patiently waiting for the next installments. I can't wait to see the outcome of the Masters plan and pray that he gets what he deserves. Miss Mary is absolutely adorable and would love to have someone like her in my life. This book was worth the wait and by not reading the snippets helped me live this book more. Thank you Lucian for another favorite in the literary world. Bravo!!</span>
