    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1399176468" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1399176468" />
    <a title="Natasha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/33997529-natasha"><img alt="Natasha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1637539063p2/33997529.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1399176468?book_show_action=true">Sep 23, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Natasha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Natasha" href="/user/show/33997529-natasha">Natasha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1399176468" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer656792077873666179">Oh my, where do I even begin? My mind has officially been blown away! <br/>I feel like I have been waiting on this book for a life time, the snippets, the teasers had dragged me in, hooked me and not for filled the craving for Solomon! However last night the teasing was over, I finally got my hands on it, and the torment still didn&apos;t stop! <br/>I finished reading at 6:15 this morning and I&apos;ve had book hangovers before but this was a whole new level, I found myself trapped within the woods of West Virginia</span>
  <span id="freeText656792077873666179" style="display:none">Oh my, where do I even begin? My mind has officially been blown away! <br />I feel like I have been waiting on this book for a life time, the snippets, the teasers had dragged me in, hooked me and not for filled the craving for Solomon! However last night the teasing was over, I finally got my hands on it, and the torment still didn't stop! <br />I finished reading at 6:15 this morning and I've had book hangovers before but this was a whole new level, I found myself trapped within the woods of West Virginia just wondering around trying to piece together the insanely what lays here. Right now I am a crazy train of emotions. <br /><br />Each time Lucian releases a new book I think how can it possibly get any better than the brilliance that has come before it, however in this case I was so awfully wrong. He has truly went to the next level with Desecrating Solomon (the first in the Desecrating series), I was captured and consumed. <br /><br />Lucian has written this story in such a way that I felt like I was there watching what was going on around me, I was experiencing everything with them,every emotion, every moment! <br />I was hooked and pulled I from the very beginning, page after page I could not stop wanting more, needing more!! The twists, the turns and the emotional battles all of which are so unpredictable, had me shocked, had me screaming and almost had my kindle take flight and I loved every single second of it all. <br />Solomon and Chaos are your primary characters and my gosh what characters they are indeed;<br /><br />Solomon has definitely become my most favourite. He is strong and yet full of kindness, he has a brilliant sense of humour that he can deliver perfectly in difficult situations. His protective nature is strong, his giving heart and undeniable innocent. All of which captivates you so much more! <br />Chaos is sheltered, uniquely different and determined but there behind the brokenness that she does not realists, is a strong willed women! Chaos has had many names, all with a strong message, unique and powerful. However within the depths of hell, will we come to realise that Chaos is in fact what she may bring or will she find a new name to fit her burning personality. <br /><br />The secondary characters in this book are incredible and every bit as powerful as Solomon and Chaos! My, my Miss Mary what can I say about her, she is amazingly quaint! She may be an elderly women but she knows her mind isn't afraid to speak it, she is strong and full of sass. <br />Mad Man Jimmy; I'm still not sure of what to make of this man. He seems to be full of wise and knowledgeable information. He stays away from human interaction, every one thinks he is crazy but you know what they say about the crazy ones. 'Crazy people are considered man by the rest of the society only because their intelligence isn't understood' <br /><br />The Luna Hills Trans Asylum what a deliciously creepy place, it's such a normal almost beautiful name for a place that should just scream 'Run, crazy lay behind these doors'. The terrifying unexpected things that are playing out before us is peek through the curtains dreading and so very intriguing.<br /><br />There are far more unanswered questions than answers that will leave you wondering until the second book. This tail is left on a cliffhanger and oh my beating heart what a cliffhanger it is, you are deliciously cruel Mr.Bane. It will drive me to insanity waiting, I will be checking myself into The Luna Hills during this time. <br /><br />I recommend is book in the highest that I can, a five isn't enough for the standards that are within this book! So if you like thrilling, pulse racing, terrifying romances then this is the book for you! I cannot spoil this read for you, it's a must have, go and see just how addicting it is for yourself. <br /><br />Thank you for sharing Lucian!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="656792077873666179" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


