<div id="review_1398437401" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1398437401" />
    <a title="Dusti Hanrahan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24901178-dusti-hanrahan"><img alt="Dusti Hanrahan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1493638299p2/24901178.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1398437401?book_show_action=true">Sep 22, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dusti Hanrahan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dusti Hanrahan" href="/user/show/24901178-dusti-hanrahan">Dusti Hanrahan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1398437401" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9818949808419515288">Wait...What the....Motherfucker....Whaaaat....SHIT!!!<br/><br/>Ok well in typical Lucian Bane fashion this book has left me feeling like I need a straight jacket.<br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1418896678ra/12939682.gif' width='400' height='350' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/> <br/><br/>This started slow for me, LB&apos;s writing has a way of making me feel a little inferior....leaving my head scrambling to piece together what the hell I am actually reading....then BAM! around half way I am speed reading, desperate to find out what happens next and praying it gives me a tiny bit of insight to a million questions..<br/><br/>The books introduce</span>
  <span id="freeText9818949808419515288" style="display:none">Wait...What the....Motherfucker....Whaaaat....SHIT!!!<br><br>Ok well in typical Lucian Bane fashion this book has left me feeling like I need a straight jacket.<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1418896678ra/12939682.gif" width="400" height="350" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br>This started slow for me, LB's writing has a way of making me feel a little inferior....leaving my head scrambling to piece together what the hell I am actually reading....then BAM! around half way I am speed reading, desperate to find out what happens next and praying it gives me a tiny bit of insight to a million questions..<br><br>The books introduces us to a fucked up cult that believes Solomon is the sacrifice for "The Desecration of Desecrations"...<br>I know right...FUCKED UP! and I can't explain anything about it because it would totally ruin the book.<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1446076024ra/16743373.gif" width="400" height="350" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>I am having sort of a love/hate thing going with this because it just wasn't great...but holy shit it was weird and insanity, asylums, cults and unbelievable sexual religious acts are in full swing so I was sucked in. <br>Just when things were piecing together...LB pulled his worst cliffhanger of all and then the fucker LAUGHED at me! <br>Damn it I need the next book! <br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1446751306ra/16890528.gif" width="300" height="250" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
