        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1426939428" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12571448443792430570"><strong>*****THIS IS A GREAT BOOK!!!! </strong><br/><br/>I came across this anonymous quote and it certainly applies to this book:<br/> &quot;A good book makes you want to live in the story.<br/> A great book gives you no choice.&quot;<br/><br/>So again I say, &quot;THIS IS A GREAT BOOK!!&quot; I lived in this story!!<br/><br/>Desecrating Solomon is a beautiful love story, yes...but don&apos;t expect all hearts and flowers in this one. There is evil lurking in the halls of the asylum and you have no idea where it&apos;s taking you! But it will suck you in, of that you can be sure!</span>
  <span id="freeText12571448443792430570" style="display:none"><strong>*****THIS IS A GREAT BOOK!!!! </strong><br /><br />I came across this anonymous quote and it certainly applies to this book:<br /> "A good book makes you want to live in the story.<br /> A great book gives you no choice."<br /><br />So again I say, "THIS IS A GREAT BOOK!!" I lived in this story!!<br /><br />Desecrating Solomon is a beautiful love story, yes...but don't expect all hearts and flowers in this one. There is evil lurking in the halls of the asylum and you have no idea where it's taking you! But it will suck you in, of that you can be sure! <br /><br />I really love the contrasting characters Lucian created for this story and the conflicts that are always present for Solomon and Chaos as they try to make sense of the differences between their beliefs and their reality. Once again Lucian has masterfully orchestrated and written a remarkable story that is difficult to leave behind. And once again he has left us dangling from a cliff with a snide remark and a haunting laugh, promising more phenomenal storytelling in the second book of the series. <br /><br />I'll leave this acrostic that sums up the storyline for me. <br /><br />Desecrating Solomon<br /><br />D arkness and<br />E vil<br />S lither and slink, <br />E ndlessly <br />C raving<br />R evenge at the<br />A sylum<br />T hat<br />I nvites <br />N othing <br />G ood<br /><br />S olomon and Chaos,<br />O bsessed with their<br />L ove, try to<br />O utsmart the<br />M aster who seeks to<br />O rdain their worst<br />N ightmare<br /><br /><br /></span>
