<div id="review_1407700475" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1407700475" />
    <a title="Suzanne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17248179-suzanne"><img alt="Suzanne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1490916953p2/17248179.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1407700475?book_show_action=true">Oct 03, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Suzanne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Suzanne" href="/user/show/17248179-suzanne">Suzanne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1407700475" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5377971846705289899">Fan Girling once again! So for those of you new to Lucian’s work, be prepared for the powerful! Desecrating Solomon (Book One of the Desecration Series)…. I thought Dom Wars was my favorite, um, yeah, I have a new favorite of Lucian’s. This is a dark and twisted story, so if you have triggers, this may not be for you. She starts out as Baby, Chosen, Silence and then finally Chaos. She is the adopted daughter of the Master, a highly frightening individual in the art of torture and mind games. Sol</span>
  <span id="freeText5377971846705289899" style="display:none">Fan Girling once again! So for those of you new to Lucian’s work, be prepared for the powerful! Desecrating Solomon (Book One of the Desecration Series)…. I thought Dom Wars was my favorite, um, yeah, I have a new favorite of Lucian’s. This is a dark and twisted story, so if you have triggers, this may not be for you. She starts out as Baby, Chosen, Silence and then finally Chaos. She is the adopted daughter of the Master, a highly frightening individual in the art of torture and mind games. Solomon, a city boy, once country kid, turned back to his home area, his wife mysteriously murdered six years prior. His town is full of secrets and back woods superstition that no one is willing to share or utter the word “desecration”. He has a gift, he can hear Chaos. They meet under extreme circumstances and together travel on a journey of transformation, flawed individuals seeking redemption. Along the way, they struggle and fight for life and love. This is book one of three, so in true Lucian form, I am impatiently waiting for the next book in Solomon and Chaos’s journey! Well written. Definitely 5 out of 5 stars and I recommend this if you like a very dark and twisted read with a bit of erotic and romance.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5377971846705289899" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


