<div id="review_1423600983" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1423600983" />
    <a title="Lisa Marie ~ Words We Love By" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21222967-lisa-marie-words-we-love-by"><img alt="Lisa Marie ~ Words We Love By" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1499701932p2/21222967.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1423600983?book_show_action=true">Oct 23, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lisa Marie ~ Words We Love By" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lisa Marie ~ Words We Love By" href="/user/show/21222967-lisa-marie-words-we-love-by">Lisa Marie ~ Words We Love By</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1423600983" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3784845883081838213"><br/>In Lucian Bane&apos;s latest offering we are introduced to Chaos and Solomon Gorge. Chaos is a deeply traumatized young woman under the thumb of the Order and Master. Mr. Bane&apos;s descriptions of her &quot; training&quot; are cringe-worthy and haunting without being way over the top. You want to smack Master with the business end of an Uzi by the end of chapter 1. Solomon is a seemingly simple guy living a simple life in backwoods West Virginia. Care-taking for Miss Mary and trapping animals. Though Solomon is f</span>
  <span id="freeText3784845883081838213" style="display:none"><br />In Lucian Bane's latest offering we are introduced to Chaos and Solomon Gorge. Chaos is a deeply traumatized young woman under the thumb of the Order and Master. Mr. Bane's descriptions of her " training" are cringe-worthy and haunting without being way over the top. You want to smack Master with the business end of an Uzi by the end of chapter 1. Solomon is a seemingly simple guy living a simple life in backwoods West Virginia. Care-taking for Miss Mary and trapping animals. Though Solomon is far from your average simple guy. Things don't remain simple for Solomon when he is targeted by the Order and finds Chaos hanging from a tree barely alive.<br /><br />This 1st part of a 3 part series gives you the basis for Solomon and Chaos' dealings with the cult and their sadistic leader, Master. The story flows quickly and sucks you in right away. There is a lot of creepy and eerie going on and you cautiously turn the page waiting for the boogeyman to jump out at you! There are far more questions than answers when you get to the cliffhanger (and what a cliff hanger it is!) But, you will definitely get pulled in.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3784845883081838213" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


