        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1407650058" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18011951588728534873">Sinister, seductive and mysterious.<br/>Gotta say this book delivers on every level.<br/>I avoided any pre-release blurbs &amp; discussions so I could just go in cold &amp; see where the story took me. <br/>Down a dark shadowed woods to a cursed asylum in a town slave to its secrets. <br/>The characters are great. Silence/Chaos is a young woman brought up by an evil twist she calls Master. Her life is pain, degradation and ritualistic abuse. Master is a dark &amp; deviant force driven by some dark calling to bring a dream/prop</span>
  <span id="freeText18011951588728534873" style="display:none">Sinister, seductive and mysterious.<br />Gotta say this book delivers on every level.<br />I avoided any pre-release blurbs &amp; discussions so I could just go in cold &amp; see where the story took me. <br />Down a dark shadowed woods to a cursed asylum in a town slave to its secrets. <br />The characters are great. Silence/Chaos is a young woman brought up by an evil twist she calls Master. Her life is pain, degradation and ritualistic abuse. Master is a dark &amp; deviant force driven by some dark calling to bring a dream/prophecy to its end. Solomon, a good man with a huge heart, who finds himself in the position of healing Chaos, saving themselves &amp; quite possibly the entire town. <br />Honestly, parts of this book struck notes of Stephen King for me. There is a thick dark oilyness that underlies even the most sweet &amp; beautiful parts of the story but doesn't overwhelm.<br />Phenomenal book!<br />Aughhhh!!!! Book 1 of 3!!!! :-)</span>
