      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/27257192-desecrating-solomon">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1422827638" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7457665160274216085">First off, I have to say I am utterly and completely mind blown right now. Lucian has taken this book to the next level, and it was all consuming. I had been waiting forever it seemed to get my hands on this book. I’ve been teased like no other, impatiently waiting for release day. And now that I’ve finish, I’m ready for more. <br/>Starting out, I was immediately sucked in. I couldn’t seem to stop reading page after page, wanting more and wanting to know what in the world was happening. There were so</span>
  <span id="freeText7457665160274216085" style="display:none">First off, I have to say I am utterly and completely mind blown right now. Lucian has taken this book to the next level, and it was all consuming. I had been waiting forever it seemed to get my hands on this book. I’ve been teased like no other, impatiently waiting for release day. And now that I’ve finish, I’m ready for more. <br />Starting out, I was immediately sucked in. I couldn’t seem to stop reading page after page, wanting more and wanting to know what in the world was happening. There were so many times I was left with my mouth hanging open, screaming why or what is happening. I was shocked to my core at the twisted situations Lucian wrote about, but at the same time, I loved every second of it. I’m a bundle of emotions and I’m left hanging, confused, and worried for what will come next. Throughout the entire book, it kept me pulled in, wondering the whole time what was going on. I’m very good at figuring out the endings of books, but with this one…yeah I’m still left wondering. It’s been a long time since I’ve read a book and it kept my interest as much as this one did. <br />Solomon has become my all-time favorite character. He’s everything you would want to see in a book like this. Strong but kind. Although he goes through some painful times in his past, he still finds himself helping others and making sure they are cared for. I loved that. Chaos, well she’s another story. I really liked her too, but I can’t even begin to explain her without giving anything away. I can’t spoil this amazing story for you guys. All I can tell you is to go buy this book. You have to see for yourself why this book is highly addictive. <br />I thought The Mercy Trilogy was my favorite from Lucian, but I’ve been proven wrong with this one. I never expected this book to literally blow my mind away and leaving me with an adrenaline rush. There are no words that are great enough for this book and I feel it’s worth more than 5 stars. Highly recommend this book and I’m back to waiting for more…Cannot wait to see what comes next! </span>
  <a data-text-id="7457665160274216085" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


