<div id="review_1808517979" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1808517979" />
    <a title="Nance" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2288023-nance"><img alt="Nance" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1614384681p2/2288023.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1808517979?book_show_action=true">Nov 18, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nance" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nance" href="/user/show/2288023-nance">Nance</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2288023-nance?shelf=e-books">e-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2288023-nance?shelf=book-boyfriends">book-boyfriends</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2288023-nance?shelf=mystery-thriller">mystery-thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2288023-nance?shelf=erotica">erotica</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2288023-nance?shelf=gothic-romance">gothic-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2288023-nance?shelf=tearjerkers">tearjerkers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2288023-nance?shelf=dark-romance">dark-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2288023-nance?shelf=books-read-2016">books-read-2016</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2288023-nance?shelf=abused-or-traumatized-characters">abused-or-traumatized-characters</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2288023-nance?shelf=religious-romance">religious-romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1808517979" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5216275145273948273"><b>4.5 star rating - I&apos;m not always a fan of short books. I&apos;m more of fan of sitting down and reading it all at once...</b><br/><br/>Warning: A bit graphic and dark...<br/><br/>Lucian Bane packs a punch from page one! This book takes off and doesn&apos;t leave the reader without questions from page one. Solomon Gorge is in for some shocking sight when he hears his name being called. What he finds, will affect him deeply. A young woman now in his care, broken and badly tortured, will make him feel nothing like he&apos;s felt before.</span>
  <span id="freeText5216275145273948273" style="display:none"><b>4.5 star rating - I'm not always a fan of short books. I'm more of fan of sitting down and reading it all at once...</b><br /><br />Warning: A bit graphic and dark...<br /><br />Lucian Bane packs a punch from page one! This book takes off and doesn't leave the reader without questions from page one. Solomon Gorge is in for some shocking sight when he hears his name being called. What he finds, will affect him deeply. A young woman now in his care, broken and badly tortured, will make him feel nothing like he's felt before. All he wants to do is take care of Chaos and protect her. But, what he eventually finds out, promises to leave horrific results.<br /><br />Solomon was one beautiful person. Looks and personality aside. He's caring and protective. With tenderness and compassion. He nurses Chaos' injuries and speaks to her with sweetness. Hums to her with affection. And, is one sensitive male. Chaos is just so messed up. Who knows what her story really is. She's just so brainwashed from the apparent abuse. It was heartbreaking to read about. But, her heart is beautiful.<br /><br />So powerful a read with so few words. The author's writing was intriguing and thrilling from the very beginning. When this installment came to an end, it was not without excitement and questions as to what will happen next with Solomon and Chaos. Now onto Part 2...</span>
  <a data-text-id="5216275145273948273" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


